==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reedling
<hw>Reed"ling</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧d"l⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The European bearded titmouse (<spn>Panurus
biarmicus</spn>); -- called also <altname>reed bunting</altname>,
<altname>bearded pinnock</altname>, and <altname>lesser butcher
bird</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is orange brown, marked with black, white, and yellow
on the wings. The male has a tuft of black feathers on each side of the
face.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reed-mace</ent>⟦br⟧
